To build you need:

1. install Android SDK and the Android NDK

2. Set ANDROID_SDK_ROOT env variable to the path where the Android SDK was installed
(most commom in Ubuntu is ~/Android/Sdk)

3. Set ANDROID_NDK env variable to the path where the Android NDK was installed

4. Accept Licences:
    $ANDROID_SDK_ROOT/tools/bin/sdkmanager --licenses

5. Run from the root of the repository ./gradlew assembleDebug


Notes:
Avaliable Android libraries can be located in the NDK by $ANDROID_NDK/platforms/android-<api-level>/arch-<architecture>/usr/lib